text:
Pro: Very attentive and engaging contact for the booking; attentive staff at the Executive Lounge; good breakfast quality (although slightly limited variety in comparison to other Hilton hotels); great views from both towers; large rooms; only 5 min. to Grand Central;

Con: Limited insulation of the windows caused a pretty cool room if you want to sleep without A/C; staff attentiveness at the breakfast in the restaurant varied; omelette were only served in the basement restaurant without windows; a cappuccino was only served for free at the Executive Lounge which also provides a great view; ongoing refurbishment in the East tower;

Major drawback: Neither during booking nor at the check-in nor with a sign at the elevators we were informed that the Executive Lounge was closed in the evenings, so we went down the East tower, crossed the lobby, went up the West tower only to realise that the Lounge was closed for "refurbishment". You could see that there were no maintenance works in the evening going on and as the Lounge was open some hours later for breakfast, the reason for the shut down was more likely to be missing staff or other things. 

In addition there was no compensation. In other Hilton hotels - in case there is no availability for an upgrade or something's going wrong - you get a voucher for the bar. If we were told before we'd have the option to book another Hilton hotel in NYC.
